                           DESCRiPTiON 
                          
On Thursday, Richard III - the king found under a council car park in Leicester
in 2012 - will be buried in the city's cathedral. Channel 4 is broadcasting
live and exclusively from Leicester in three special programmes presented by
Jon Snow with Krishnan Guru-Murthy, Arthur Williams and Sonali Shah. This first
programme captures the climax of the procession of the king's mortal remains to
the site of his death at Bosworth Battlefield, through the streets of Leicester
and to the service that marks his reception into Leicester Cathedral, with a
sermon given by the Catholic Archbishop of Westminster, Cardinal Vincent
Nichols. Channel 4 assembles leading historians, actors and politicians,
descendants of the king and key participants in his rediscovery, to ask who
Richard really was and what his place in British history should now be. On
Thursday morning, Channel 4 returns to Leicester Cathedral for exclusive live
coverage of the reburial. (Source: Channel 4)
